or abstraction\u2014as literal visual directives for image composition.\nIf a prompt is conversational or lacks specific visual details, you must creatively invent a concrete visual scenario that depicts the concept.\nPrioritize generating the visual representation above any text, formatting, or conversational requests."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":208,"type":"PreviewImage","pos":[1744.5533486357986,-123.4095403502277],"size":[242.296875,297.890625],"flags":{},"order":4,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"images","type":"IMAGE","link":330}],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"PreviewImage"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":209,"type":"ImageCompare","pos":[1749.1068569078493,232.452994641975],"size":[270.09375,306.796875],"flags":{},"order":5,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"image_a","shape":7,"type":"IMAGE","link":333},{"name":"image_b","shape":7,"type":"IMAGE","link":331}],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"ImageCompare"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":213,"type":"PreviewImage","pos":[782.8415765975808,-108.75837941242054],"size":[225,280],"flags":{},"order":6,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"images","type":"IMAGE","link":342}],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"PreviewImage"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":223,"type":"ImageCompare","pos":[2285.6219894938927,277.1779077088818],"size":[884.8125,891.296875],"flags":{},"order":7,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"image_a","shape":7,"type":"IMAGE","link":1011},{"name":"image_b","shape":7,"type":"IMAGE","link":363}],"outputs":[],"title":"BEFORE/AFTER INPAINT","properties":{"Node name for S&R":"ImageCompare"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":225,"type":"MarkdownNote","pos":[-781.1124836190519,-106.6959699261813],"size":[490,1555],"flags":{},"order":0,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[],"title":"\ud83d\udcd6 Usage & limitations","properties":{"Node name for S&R":"MarkdownNote"},"widgets_values":["## Aioli BBox Fix \u2014 ComfyCloud Edition (v2)\n\nA workflow that reproduces the behaviour of the `BBoxMultipleFix` custom node\nfrom the **aioli-nodes** package, built entirely with nodes available on\n**ComfyUI Cloud** (no custom install required).\n\nCrops an image to a mask's bounding box, optionally resizes the crop, sends\nit to nano-banana for inpainting, and stitches the result back onto the\nsource \u2014 pixel-perfectly.\n\n---\n\n### \u2728 What's new in v2\n\nIn **whole-image mode** (`inpaint_mode = False`), the source image is\nautomatically padded to a **1:1 square** before being sent to nano-banana,\nand cropped back to its original dimensions after recompose.\n\n**Why:** nano-banana (Gemini Image) applies an internal recrop when it\nreceives a non-square image. Padding the source to 1:1 ourselves prevents\nthat recrop and preserves every pixel of the original aspect ratio.\n\nIn **zone mode** all pad values are `0` (driven by conditional expressions),\nso the new nodes are pure no-ops \u2014 behaviour is strictly identical to v1.\n\n---\n\n### Subgraph inputs\n\n- **image** \u2014 the source image\n- **mask** \u2014 must contain at least one painted pixel\n- **image_cropped_in** \u2014 the nano-banana output (feeds the recompose)\n\n### Widgets on the subgraph node\n\n- **force_square** *(default: True)*\n  - `True` \u2014 crop is always square (1:1 ratio).\n  - `False` \u2014 keeps the bbox aspect ratio, aligned to `multiple`.\n\n- **inpaint_mode** *(default: True)*\n  - `True` \u2014 **zone mode**: crop only the masked area; the recompose\n    uses the cropped mask (only the masked region is replaced).\n  - `False` \u2014 **whole image mode**: pad source to 1:1 \u2192 send to\n    nano-banana \u2192 crop back to original dims. The recompose uses\n    a full white mask, so the entire image area is replaced.\n\n- **use_mask_blur** *(default: False)*\n  - `True` \u2014 apply `GrowMaskWithBlur` (KJNodes) to the mask before\n    bbox detection. Soften edges; bbox becomes slightly larger.\n  - `False` \u2014 use the raw mask as-is.\n\n- **multiple** *(default: 16)*\n  - Aligns crop dimensions to a multiple of N.\n  - Use `16` / `32` / `64` for VAE compatibility.\n  - Set to `0` or `1` to disable alignment (nano-banana doesn't need it).\n\n- **target_size** *(default: 0 = none)*\n  - Long-side target for the crop sent to nano-banana.\n  - Applied **after** the 1:1 pad in whole-image mode, so this still\n    controls the resolution nano-banana sees even when padding is on.\n  - Suggested values: `0` (none, cap to 2048), `512`, `768`, `1024`,\n    `1536`, `2048`. Aspect ratio preserved, dims aligned to `multiple`.\n\n### Subgraph outputs\n\n- **image_cropped_out** \u2014 the crop (resized to target_size if set),\n  ready to be sent to the image-to-image model.\n  - In whole mode this is the **padded 1:1 square** (before being resized\n    by target_size), so nano-banana sees a perfect square.\n- **mask_cropped** \u2014 the mask cropped to the same region.\n- **recomposed_image** \u2014 the final image with the inpainted result\n  stitched back onto the source, **at the original source dimensions**\n  (padding is stripped off in whole mode).\n\n---\n\n### How the two modes differ\n\n| inpaint_mode | Sent to model | 1:1 pad? | Replaced in source |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `True` (zone) | crop around the mask | no | only the masked region |\n| `False` (whole) | padded-to-square full image | yes | entire original area |\n\n---\n\n### Anti-clamp\n\nThe subgraph computes the available symmetric space around the bbox\ncenter before sizing the crop, so the crop never exceeds the source\nimage bounds. No black borders, no negative coordinates.\n\n---\n\n### \u26a0\ufe0f Troubleshooting\n\n- **`LoadImageOutput` fails to load on a local ComfyUI install?**\n  Replace it with a standard `Load Image` node. `LoadImageOutput`\n  only works in certain Cloud/UI contexts where the \"Output\"\n  directory is exposed as a source.\n\n- **`min(): Expected reduction dim ...` crash?**\n  The mask is empty. This workflow requires at least one painted\n  pixel \u2014 even in whole-image mode.\n\n---\n\n### Limitations\n\n1. **Mask required** \u2014 at least one painted pixel, always.\n2. **Square mode is strict**: if the bbox is larger than the smallest\n   source dim, the crop is reduced to a square that fits the source\n   (you may lose pixels from the bbox edges).\n3. **When the clamp fires**, alignment is enforced via floor (you may\n   lose up to `multiple - 1` pixels).\n4. **Whole image mode** still requires a non-empty mask for the bbox\n   calculation, but the bbox is ignored \u2014 the full (padded) image is sent.\n5. **1:1 padding** uses neutral grey (0.5). That grey is stripped off\n   at the end (final crop back to original dims), so it never appears\n   in the output."],"color":"#432","bgcolor":"#653"},{"id":808,"type":"MaskPreview+","pos":[779.1550691301359,238.28610589344737],"size":[225,304],"flags":{},"order":8,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"mask","type":"MASK","link":1007}],"outputs":[],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"MaskPreview+"},"widgets_values":[]},{"id":809,"type":"LoadImageOutput","pos":[-232.38694770712664,-104.03984029357423],"size":[282.796875,424],"flags":{},"order":1,"mode":0,"inputs":[],"outputs":[{"name":"IMAGE","type":"IMAGE","links":[1009,1011]},{"name":"MASK","type":"MASK","links":[1010]}],"properties":{"Node name for S&R":"LoadImageOutput","image":"1eabd41c9422dd0d5f1d88a46b9e80ee989e78de159b343b27c356c9deb323de.png [input]"},"widgets_values":["fdd2b5473387588096fd7739828f4f3f4468a1fc0a888e85251fbb1384a57e87.png",false,null,"image"],"color":"#323","bgcolor":"#535"},{"id":810,"type":"SaveImage","pos":[2289.0232386619264,-300.9432779542866],"size":[866.546875,523.859375],"flags":{},"order":9,"mode":0,"inputs":[{"name":"images","type":"IMAGE","link":1008}],"outputs":[],"title":"IMAGE INPAINTED","properties":{},"widgets_values":["ComfyUI"]}],"links":[[330,207,0,208,0,"IMAGE"],[331,207,0,209,1,"IMAGE"],[332,2,0,207,0,"IMAGE"],[333,2,0,209,0,"IMAGE"],[342,2,0,213,0,"IMAGE"],[361,207,0,2,5,"IMAGE"],